^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Very nicely played. One comment on the defense before we get to the bidding. When you were in with the @SJ Nada, why didn't you lead a heart to start trick nine? If you had, Eddy might have finessed the spade and you might have scored your @SK. Never be afraid to give the declarer a ruff to which he is entitled anyway. At worst that is a passive play. It does not give anything away and, in this case, it might help you score your @SK. If you cannot prevent the ruff anyway, it usually gives nothing away to give declarer a ruff.|
