^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Some people play a convention known as a "support double", which works very well here. Support doubles work as follows. If the auction goes 1 minor - p - 1 major - overcall, a double by opener is not penalty. It shows exactly 3-card support for responder's major. So, on this hand, playing support doubles, it would go 1C-P-1S-2H-dbl and Eddy would know I have exactly 3-card support. With 4-card support I bid 2S. |
PG| ***** 67 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|People also extend that convention to support redoubles, the relevant auction being 1C-P-1S-dbl-redbl which also showing 3-card support. With interference, assuming no support doubles, very often partner will be forced to compete with 3-card support.|
