cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|You are forcing a spade honor out by playing low as well. If zewzew plays low, then you win the Jack. If she plays high, you have forced out an honor, and still have the Jack and 10 left to force out whichever honor is still missing. The way you played it, unless Nada has both the K and Q, you are only guaranteed 1 spade trick.|
PG| ***** 104 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Another declarer play technique issue. When you are running a long suit, in this case diamonds you typically play out the honors from the shorter hand first, in this case South. The reason for that is, that way you make sure you do not block the suit. The way Marge played it, where she cashed the @DA in her hand first, she blocked the suit, she could not get to her @DJ without wasting an entry.|
