^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Okay, now let's discuss Roberta's play of the hand. Let's look at her losers. She has 1 or 2 heart losers, possibly a spade loser, and 1 or 2 club losers. That is 4-6 losers. Given Anna preempted, it is much more likely she is short in spades and Roberta only probably has 1 entry to dummy. Unless Anna has the @HK, which is not likely. So, the spade finesse is absolutely correct. If it makes you feel any better Roberta, even if Anna gets out with a diamond instead of a club, you lose 2 clubs and 2 hearts and go down anyway. So, no matter what you do you are down.|
