NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|However, if the opponents are at the 3-level you should only bid "3 over 3" if you have a 9-card fit, or you have a singleton or void in their suit. I think, particularly given Stan has no points in spades, a negative double is ok. If you had opened 1H, even assuming no Bergen raises he bids 2H.|
