NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|As to the play, although normally second hand low is correct when Roberta leads a diamond off the board, Anna should know the diamond position. Partner led high low. Since partner did not support the suit, he would lead low from 3 small. Therefore, Roberta has the 9 left and Stan is out and then Anna has to cash hearts right away before Roberta throws them on the @D10. So, take the @DJ, and then play Ace and the Jack of hearts.|
